<html><head></head><body><b>Pierre Curie (1859–1906)</b><br/>
French physicist. <br/>He demonstrated <br/>the phenomenon <br/>of piezoelectricity in 1880, isolated new elements<br/> – radium and polonium, <br/>and in 1903 was granted <br/>the Nobel Prize for his research on the radiation phenomena discovered <br/>by Professor Henri Becquerel. Pierre Curie was the first person to conduct on himself medical experiments <br/>with radioactive radium.
</body></html>